The paper focuses on the task of language understanding using recurrent neural networks, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new model that uses external memory to improve the memory capacity of RNNs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses the ATIS dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset for NLP tasks, and may involve some image processing techniques for data visualization, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category.
